news.title: Property owners fret as technology glitches hold up registries at tehsil offices in Gurugram
news.para: There are six tehsils - Gurugram, Manesar, Pataudi, Farukhnagar, Sohna and Wazirabad - and three sub-tehsils - Harsaru, Kadipur and Badshapur - in the city.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority registers FIR against 50 for developing illegal colonies in Tappal
news.para: On November 9, YEIDA carried out the demolition drive in Tappal and freed over 15 hectares of land, the market price of which is pegged at Rs 230 crore.

news.title: Submit plan to clear illegal colonies in Noida along Hindon banks, agencies told
news.para: The four agencies will also have to make plans to increase the green cover in the Hindon floodplains under the provisions of the Noida and Greater Noida master plans.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents demand structural & financial audits of New Town Heights
news.para: In a letter to DTCP director general TL Satyaprakash, deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav and district town planner Amit Madholia, residents have alleged that poor design and construction flaws pose a safety risk to 600 families living in the society.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth 78 crore in Heera Gold scam
news.para: ED sleuths stumbled upon Nowhera Sheik and her Heera Group of companies transferring 148 crore to SA Builders and Developers for purchasing properties in Tolichowki.

news.title: Poonawalla Fincorp sells housing finance arm to TPG for Rs 3,900 crore
news.para: ​The transaction, subject to regulatory approvals, is being carried out by TPG global arm Perseus SG, the statement said, adding the deal will is part of its effort to maximise shareholder value and to focus on consumer and MSME financing by building a tech-led financial services company.

news.title: MahaRERA asks 13 districts to ensure buyers get Rs 730 crore in compensations
news.para: ​The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRera) has also appointed a retired additional district collector to follow-up in such cases where dues have been pending, an official statement said.

news.title: Haryana RERA imposes Rs 2.5 crore penalty on Brahma City
news.para: ​​The authority has asked the promoter of the project, Brahma City Private Limited, to deposit the penalty within one month from the date of issuance of this notice.

news.title: Sebi planning 'micro' REITs to boost nascent market: Source
news.para: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) is considering reducing the size of REITs, allowing them to hold just a single asset or a diversified portfolio, to increase supply and flexibility for investors, said the official.

news.title: Shriram Properties acquires Golden Gates' stressed project in Bengaluru
news.para: The transaction involves capital commitments of up to Rs 125 crore towards the acquisition and development of the project. SPL plans to rename and launch the project as Shriram Pristine Estates.

news.title: Gurugram: Rent not paid, HSVP seals 12 shops, to auction them
news.para: The HSVP team sealed shop numbers 25, 60, 135, 145 and 146 in Sector 22 market, while in the Sector 23A market shop numbers 65, 66, 67, 69, 102, 103 and 104 were shut.

news.title: Small flat blocks get a shock over common area power bills
news.para: At six-unit apartment block in Perungudi used to pay 100 for the common area connection. The latest bill is 2,520. At another apartment block in Pattabiram, the latest common area power bill was ₹2,600, four times what they paid in the previous bill.

news.title: Kerala: 482 plots in five panchayats fall within ESZ, says report
news.para: In the wake of the expert committee publishing the preliminary report on areas falling in the eco-sensitive zones (ESZ) of Neyyar and Peppara wildlife sanctuaries, the Amboori panchayat — which has the highest number of areas within the ESZ — convened an emergency steering

news.title: JMC-Greater deputy mayor raises issue of Rs 400 crore dues from Rajasthan housing board
news.para: The RHB on Monday gave an amount of Rs 23.23 crore to JMC-Greater for development works. This is the first time in 15 years, that the RHB gave the 15% of its earnings to JMC-Greater, as stated in the provisions.

news.title: North East governments rush to meet new PMAY-Gramin deadline
news.para: Sadhvi Niranjan Jyoti informed while about 85% of the 2.49 crore houses sanctioned by various states and Union territories under PMAY-G scheme have been completed nationally, 50% to 80% of the sanctioned houses remain incomplete in the northeast.
